  <!-- PAGE 2 -->
  <section id="page2" class="section">
    <h2>KSA Jobs Blog</h2>
    <p>
      Saudi Arabia continues to attract thousands of expats every year due to its stable economy, strong job demand, and tax‑free income. Most workers come for better salaries and long‑term financial stability.
    </p>
    <p>
      Common job sectors include construction, driving, cleaning, security, hospitality, retail, and skilled labor. Salaries vary depending on company, city, experience, and work type. Entry‑level jobs may start from 1200–1800 SAR, while skilled roles can range between 2500–5000 SAR or more.
    </p>
    <p>
      Living costs in Saudi Arabia depend heavily on accommodation and food choices. Shared rooms are more affordable, while private apartments can be expensive depending on the city. Workers often save more by cooking at home and using shared transportation.
    </p>
    <p>
      Overall, KSA remains a good option for people looking for stable jobs and long‑term savings. Understanding salary packages, company benefits, and lifestyle costs can help workers plan better before arriving.
    </p>
  </section>
